<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CATERPILLAR 3176B AND 3406E ELECTRONIC ENGINES - DIAGNOSTICS AND TROUBLESHOOTING - SERVICE/CHECK
        ENGINE LIGHT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SERVICE/CHECK ENGINE LIGHT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>"Service/Check Engine Light" Does Not Turn ON</title>
            <para>This test should be performed if the light does not turn ON during the self test.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check Serv/Check Engine light bulb for open filament before beginning this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0805714" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 8 - "Service/Check Engine Light" Does Not Turn ON</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <thead valign="bottom">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">"SERVICE/CHECK ENGINE LIGHT" DOES NOT TURN ON</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (400) from the ECM. Turn key ON and measure voltage to gnd at
                                    terminal 6.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>11.0 to 13.5 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Perform test 6.3.5.1.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (400) use test lead and jumper terminal 27 to gnd. Service/check
                                    engine light should turn ON and remain ON while circuit is grounded. Is light ON?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Have Caterpillar dealer diagnose the ECM.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AZ between connector (423) and (400)
                                    and repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>"Service/Check Engine Light" Stays ON or Comes ON Intermittently</title>
            <para>This test should be performed if the light stays ON or comes ON intermittently.</para>
            <para>If the light comes ON intermittently, check for logged codes, because the light comes ON briefly while
                codes are active.
            </para>
            <para>If the complaint is related to the light continually flashing diagnostic codes (without operator
                prompting), the Cruise Set/Resume Switch circuit may be shorted to ground.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check Serv/Check Engine light bulb for open filament before beginning this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
